Here are some things to remember:

cd <folder> - Change directory to that folder
cd .. - Go to the parent folder
cd ~ - Go to home folder

ls - List files in current directory
ls -a - List all files including hidden files
ls -l - List files with details

rm <file> - Remove file
rm -R <folder> - Remove folder and all its contents (the R stands for recursive)

git pull - Pulls changes from remote repository
git push origin master - Push changes to remote repository
git add <file> - Add file to be tracked
git commit -m "<message>" - Commits changes

